<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-686-480  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 686 480.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Design  August 24 1989 v37 n18 p20(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tiny optical sensor takes temperature, pressure measurements.andO;(Metricor's ColorOptic system)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Leonard, Milt.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Metricor's ColorOptic system solves the problems of processcontrol associated with fiberglass-epoxy composite pultrusionmolding.andP;  Maximum accuracy of pressure and temperature arerequired during molding and curing and can only be achieved byimmersing the sensors into the composite.andP;  Conventional sensorsare too large.andP;  ColorOptic uses microminiature sensors connectedby multimode fiber-optic leads.andP;  The measurement channel is madeup of an 850-nanometer LED source, two photodiodes, a beamsplitter and a sensor probe measuring only 0.032 inches across and0.4 inches long connected by a fiber-optic cable.andP;  This probeplugs into a four-channel instrument containing data-acquisitioncircuits for signal processing.andP;  Results of the pressure andtemperature measurements appear both on a vacuum-fluorescentdisplay and at analog and digital outputs.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Metricor Inc. (manufactures).andO;Product:   Metricor ColorOptic (Measuring instruments) (productspecifications).andO;Topic:     Optoelectronic devicesProcess controlPlastics IndustrySensors.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   (Metricolor's ColorOptic technique). (chart)(This sensor). (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>